<title>UK: Next off on negative comments from Hoare.</title>
<headline>Next off on negative comments from Hoare.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Next Plc led most other retail stocks lower on Monday after brokerage ABN AMRO Hoare Govett made cautious comments on the stock, dealers said.</p>
<p>At 1107 GMT, Next shares were trading at 620-1/2, down 11p on the day and off 24-1/2p, or 3.8 percent, from their April 10 closing peak.  </p>
<p>Emma Burdett, ABN AMRO Hoare Govett stores analyst, wasn't immediately available to comment.</p>
